[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] A single edge appearing in the optimal solution is removed from the graph, and the optimum solution to this new graph is calculated.
[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] Each edge of the original solution is suppressed in turn and a new shortest-path calculated.
[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] The secondary solutions are then ranked and presented after the first optimal solution.
