[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] The A* algorithm is a generalization of Dijkstra's algorithm that reduces the size of the subgraph that must be explored, if additional information is available that provides a lower bound on the distance to the target.
[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] The process that underlies Dijkstra's algorithm is similar to the greedy process used in Prim's algorithm.
