[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] The fast marching method can be viewed as a continuous version of Dijkstra's algorithm which computes the geodesic distance on a triangle mesh.
[src:graph-algorithms/dijkstra-s-algorithm] From a dynamic programming point of view, Dijkstra's algorithm is a successive approximation scheme that solves the dynamic programming functional equation for the shortest path problem by the **Reaching** method.
